raw_data.name: Mother of Dragons
raw_data.full_address: 1640 Sardis Rd N STE 110, Charlotte, NC 28270, United States

reviews_data.review_text: Great crew! Great coffee and beer! Awesome space. Thanks for creating a cool space to hang
Very cool spot if you are into board games, good music, and good wine

Had a fantastic evening at Mother of Dragons. Wife and I went for a date night and had a great time. Some interesting new games to try and the recommendations from the staff were perfect. The food and drinks were amazing and really a step above what I expected for a gaming evening. Planning to stop by again soon during lunch with some work friends. Prices were fair, and the vibe is perfect for either a casual hangout or a nice evening out. Great place to have nearby.

Such a cool place for the whole family!
Yummy food and drinks, and so many games to choose from. The owner and staff are also so nice. We played scrabble, drank wine, and I left with a new Hello kitty monopoly. Can’t wait to come back for one of their gaming events.

Family went and brought our own game but will go back and buy a game.  Great selection to borrow also.  I went during a wine tasting and enjoyed the wine.  Food was good too.  Staff was very inviting.

A stylish space for gaming and drinks. They specialize in 3 aspects:
1. Games: large rental library, and knowledgeable staff to teach you how to play. They'll also help you clean up, which is a huge bonus. Plenty of TCG packs like pokémon for purchase. Doing the whole thing. Lots of tables and even a private space for all sorts of games.
2. Coffee: incredibly reasonable prices for such a curated collection of beans. Quit that with you right now. Selection of locally made baked goods to go with it, Even the option to do a really cool omakase coffee tasting.
3. Wine: What a great selection for a game store, with highly curated bottles. Everything from interesting reds to funky bubbles.

I'm excited to Keep coming here and having fun with my family.

reviews_data.review_text: What a fantastic addition to the area. An all ages  place for family fun or just to hang out with like minded people. They offer a rather large selection of board games, and drinks. The owner Vince, is super nice. If you are looking for a great atmosphere and a place to have a friends night, or even great pour over coffee please stop by and give them a visit, it's worth it!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Bar area, Booth seating, Counter seating

reviews_data.review_text: Came in for games but stayed for the wine list! So excited to have this spot local to us. They somehow manage to be geeky but cool at the same time. Amazing collection of games to play, games to buy, food to eat and wine to try… 🥰
Very cute place! They have games for all levels  and a great wine selection!

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Great atmosphere and love the concept with the multitude of games. Really good wine selection withe very knowledgable staff.
Lovely spot for games, wine, beer fun drinks and nibbles. 👍👍 brought the kids but will be back with friends too!
Fun for the entire fam! Friendly staff and great ambiance.

Been waiting for this place to open up it looks really nice had a pleasant and informative conversation with the staff. Looks like a nice place to bring a couple of friends just to hang out and play. 10/10 ambiance. Will be coming back to check out more things it has to offer. And they are cashless.

Just popped in to check them out 3 days after their official opening and was impressed. Great high quality selection of games, beverages, and bites. Staff was really friendly and it was clear the owners curated things to deliver the best experience possible for their customers. Highly recommend stopping in.
Amazing selection of games (for all ages), great coffee, relaxing decor & atmosphere

A fantastic way to enjoy great board games and spend quality time with family and friends. An amazing, well-designed atmosphere with a sophisticated ambiance. A comfortable, relaxing café with a deep library of high-rated games and a classy menu from great wines and charcuterie boards, to draft beers and top-notch coffees. Vanessa and Tony are very friendly, well-knowledgeable baristas! They've got you covered. Don't pass up an opportunity to have a great time in this unique new experience! AAA+++
Excellent service everyone here is so kind, welcoming and just extraordinary, COFFEE IS AMAZING AS WELL NEVER TRIED SOMETHING LIKE THIS BEFORE

This place is great for families to have an alternative to playing games, enjoying beverages and light bites to eat.

Highly recommend seeking this out as it's a great concept to allow families to spend time together
